## TypeScript rules

- Strict mode is on — no `any`, no `as any`, no type assertions without justification
- All API route handlers must be typed with NextRequest and NextResponse
- All Zustand stores must have a typed interface before the create() call
- All Prisma query results must be typed — use the generated Prisma types
- All Claude API responses must be parsed with try/catch and validated before use
- Environment variables must be accessed as process.env.VAR_NAME with ! or null checks
- Never use NEXT_PUBLIC_ prefix except for NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL (the only safe client variable)

## Environment variables — complete list

Required in .env.local (never commit this file):

  ANTHROPIC_API_KEY          # From console.anthropic.com — server only
  NOTION_CLIENT_ID           # From notion.so/my-integrations — server only
  NOTION_CLIENT_SECRET       # From notion.so/my-integrations — server only
  NOTION_REDIRECT_URI        # http://localhost:3000/api/auth/callback (dev)
  DATABASE_URL               # From Supabase → Settings → Database → URI
  SESSION_SECRET             # 64-char hex — generate with crypto.randomBytes(32)
  ENCRYPTION_KEY             # 64-char hex — DIFFERENT value from SESSION_SECRET
  VAPID_PUBLIC_KEY           # From: npx web-push generate-vapid-keys
  VAPID_PRIVATE_KEY          # From: npx web-push generate-vapid-keys
  VAPID_SUBJECT              # mailto:your@email.com
  CRON_SECRET                # 64-char hex — protects /api/push/send from public access
  NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL        # http://localhost:3000 (dev) / https://yourdomain.com (prod)

SESSION_SECRET and ENCRYPTION_KEY must be different values — never reuse.
CRON_SECRET is checked in /api/push/send via: req.headers.get('x-cron-secret')

## Security rules — never violate these

- ANTHROPIC_API_KEY must never appear in client-side code or NEXT_PUBLIC_ variables
- NOTION_CLIENT_SECRET must never appear in client-side code
- Notion access tokens are stored AES-256 encrypted in the database — use lib/encrypt.ts
- All API routes must check session authentication before doing anything else
- Session cookies must be httpOnly: true, secure: true (in production), sameSite: 'strict'
- Image data (base64) from photo captures must never be stored — pass directly to Claude and discard
- /api/push/send must check x-cron-secret header before processing — return 401 if missing or wrong
- Rate limit /api/capture: max 60 requests per user per hour — use in-memory counter or Upstash Redis

## The AI capture endpoint — /api/capture/route.ts

This is the most important file. Rules:
- One Claude API call per capture — never split into multiple calls
- Model: claude-sonnet-4-20250514 (never change this without asking)
- System prompt is built dynamically per user from their PageConfig entries
- For text/voice: user message is the raw input string
- For photo: user message is an image content block with base64 JPEG
- Response is always parsed as JSON — wrap in try/catch
- For photo mode: response is an array of task objects
- max_tokens: 1024 is sufficient — never increase without reason
- The system prompt template lives in nevermist-system-prompt.txt at project root
- Input sanitisation: strip HTML tags and null bytes before sending to Claude
  inputValue.replace(/<[^>]*>/g, '').replace(/\0/g, '').slice(0, 500)
- Image validation before compression: check file.size < 20MB and
  ['image/jpeg','image/png','image/webp'].includes(file.type)

## Notion integration rules

Two types of Notion destinations — handle both:

1. Notion Database (isDatabase: true in PageConfig):
   - Create entry: POST /v1/pages with parent: { database_id }
   - Set properties: Title, Priority (Select), Due Date (Date), Created (auto)
   - Property mapping is stored in PageConfig.databaseProps as JSON

2. Notion Plain Page (isDatabase: false in PageConfig):
   - Create entry: PATCH /v1/blocks/{pageId}/children
   - Append a to_do block with the task text
   - Embed metadata inline: "Task text [P2] [Due: Mar 20]"

Always use @notionhq/client — never raw fetch to Notion API.
Always decrypt the Notion token before use: decrypt(user.notionToken)

## State management — Zustand store rules

Four stores, four jobs:

useCaptureStore: inputValue, inputMode ('text'|'voice'|'photo'|'url'), isProcessing, processingError
usePreviewStore: visible, cleanedTask, destinationPageId, destinationName, priority, dueDate, isRecurring, recurringPattern, isUrl, sourceUrl, tasks (array for photo mode)
useQueueStore: items (QueueItem[]), isSyncing, isOnline, failedItems (FailedItem[])
useUserStore: isAuthenticated, notionWorkspace, pages (PageConfig[]), textPolish, nudgeTime, hasCompletedFirstCapture, hasSeenTagline

Rules:
- Never access store state directly in components — always use the store hook
- Never put API calls inside stores — API calls belong in hooks (useCapture.ts etc.)
- Reset useCaptureStore and usePreviewStore after every successful send
- useQueueStore.isOnline syncs with navigator.onLine

## Offline queue rules

- Save to IndexedDB BEFORE making any API call — not after
- Use lib/offline-queue.ts for all IndexedDB operations (addToQueue, getAllQueued, removeFromQueue, markFailed)
- Sync is sequential — process one item at a time, never parallel
- Error handling:
  - 401 (auth revoked) → stop entire sync, show reconnect banner
  - 404 (page deleted) → skip item, mark as failed, continue sync
  - 429 (rate limit) → pause, retry with exponential backoff (2s, 4s, 8s)
  - Network drop → stop, resume on next online event
- Never delete a queue item until receiving a confirmed 200 from Notion API
- Show StatusPill with count of queued items when offline

## Component rules

- All components are client components ('use client') unless they fetch data — then server components
- CaptureInput must always be focused on mount — use autoFocus or ref.focus()
- SendButton opacity: 0 when input is empty, opacity: 1 when input has content — use CSS transition not conditional rendering (avoids layout shift)
- PreviewCard uses AnimatePresence from Framer Motion — mount/unmount with slide-up animation
- ConfirmationToast auto-dismisses after 5000ms — use setTimeout in useEffect, clear on unmount
- PagePickerSheet is a bottom sheet on mobile, dropdown on desktop — use @radix-ui/react-dialog
- Never use position: fixed for any component — use position: sticky or normal flow

## Image compression rules — always compress before Claude

In lib/camera.ts — compressImage() function:
- Validate first: file.size < 20MB AND type in ['image/jpeg','image/png','image/webp']
- Max dimension: 1600px (longest side)
- Format: JPEG
- Quality: 0.8
- Method: canvas drawImage then toBlob
- Target output: 150–300KB
- Never send uncompressed photos to the API — upload time and cost matter

## Design system — use these exact values

Colors (as Tailwind arbitrary values or CSS variables):
- Background: bg-[#0A0A0A]      (main bg)
- Surface:     bg-[#121212]     (cards, input area)
- Card:        bg-[#1A1A1A]     (preview card, toast)
- Border:      border-[#2E2E2E] (default)
- Text primary: text-[#EDEAE4]
- Text muted:   text-[#8A847C]
- Text dim:     text-[#454240]
- Amber accent: text-[#C49A6C] / border-[#C49A6C]  (focus, active, cursor)
- Sage accent:  text-[#6BA888] / border-[#6BA888]  (Notion, confirmed, done)
- P1 priority:  text-[#B86B5A] bg-[#1E0E0A]
- P2 priority:  text-[#C4944A] bg-[#1E1608]
- Orange badge: #E8773A (camera icon dot only)

Fonts (set in layout.tsx via Google Fonts):
- Lora (serif)   — user content: input text, task text, extracted items, main headline
- DM Sans        — UI labels, descriptions, body text, confirmation messages
- DM Mono        — tags, send button, status pill, screen labels, metadata, system chrome

Input styling — the signature detail:
- border-l-[1.5px] border-[#2E2E2E] (resting)
- focus:border-[#C49A6C] transition-colors duration-[250ms] (focused)
- No box, no background, no border-radius — left border ONLY
- caret-color: #C49A6C (amber cursor)
- padding-left: 20px (text indented from border)

Animation values (use in Framer Motion):
- Preview card slide-up: initial={{y:"100%",opacity:0}} animate={{y:0,opacity:1}} transition={{duration:0.3,ease:[0.16,1,0.3,1]}}
- Toast: same as above but duration 0.25
- Send button: initial={{opacity:0}} animate={{opacity: hasContent ? 1 : 0}} transition={{duration:0.15}}
- Cancel / card exit: scale 0.95 + opacity 0, duration 0.2, ease:"easeIn"
- Page load stagger: each element 100ms apart, 600ms ease-out, opacity 0→1 + translateY 10px→0
- Voice pulse: scale 1→1.15→1, 1.2s loop ease-in-out
- Voice ring: opacity 0.3→0 + scale 1→2, 1.2s loop ease-out
All animations must use useReducedMotion() from Framer Motion — skip if true.

