## Naming conventions

Files: PascalCase for components (CaptureInput.tsx), camelCase for utilities (offline-queue.ts)
Functions: camelCase (buildSystemPrompt, compressImage, addToQueue)
Types/Interfaces: PascalCase (CaptureResult, PageConfig, QueueItem)
Zustand stores: useCaptureStore, usePreviewStore, useQueueStore, useUserStore
API routes: always route.ts inside a folder matching the URL path
Environment variables: SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE

## What NOT to do — ever

- Do not add a navigation bar, header menu, or bottom tab bar — one screen only
- Do not show task history in the app — the app is not a task viewer
- Do not add a "clear all" or "manage queue" UI — the queue is silent
- Do not show the AI Polish toggle per-capture — it belongs in Settings only
- Do not store any task content in the database — it flows to Notion and is discarded
- Do not call the Anthropic API or Notion API from the client — server-side only
- Do not use window.localStorage for offline queue — use IndexedDB via idb
- Do not make the confirmation toast dismissible by clicking — it auto-dismisses after 5s
- Do not add animations that don't respect prefers-reduced-motion
- Do not change the model from claude-sonnet-4-20250514 without discussion
- Do not send unvalidated or unsanitised input to the Claude API
- Do not expose raw API error messages to the client — always return user-friendly copy
- Do not skip the CRON_SECRET check on /api/push/send

## When you are unsure

If a feature, pattern, or architectural decision is not covered in these rules:
1. Check docs/design-doc.md first
2. Check docs/prd.md second
3. Check docs/tech-stack.md third
4. If still unclear — ask before implementing

The three reference documents are the source of truth.
These rules are a compressed version of what is in those documents.